  "texts": [
    "The primary pre-training objectives are categorized into three types:Code-test Alignment Learning.",
    "The core idea is to explicitly teach the model the semantic and structural mapping between the code under test (CUT) and its corresponding test code.",
    "CAT-LM [115] stands as a landmark work, training a 2.7 billion parameter model on 1.1 million code-test pairs using a special <|codetestpair|> separator.",
    "While this work demonstrated the significant potential of alignment learning, it came at a high cost, as the entire training process required 8 NVIDIA A100 80GB GPUs for 18 days, with an estimated cost of $20,000.Task-specific Self-supervised Learning.",
    "This approach employs proxy tasks related to test generation subtasks for pre-training."
  ],
